## ⏱️ Complexity Analysis

| Approach | Time | Space (extra) |
|----------|------|----------------|
| Brute Force | `O(n²)` — inner loop re-traverses each prefix | `O(1)` |
| **Optimal (Prefix Sum)** | **`O(n)`** — build prefix in O(n), then O(1) work per index | **`O(n)`** — for the prefix array |

The optimal approach trades a little extra space (the prefix array) for a massive time improvement — from quadratic to linear — which is the right trade-off for almost every interview setting and for large `n`.

---

## 🔑 Key Interview Points

**Why median?**
Because the median minimizes `Σ |arr[i] - x|` — this is a fact worth memorizing cold; it comes up across many "minimum operations to equalize" style problems.

**Why prefix sum?**
To compute left-sum and right-sum of any prefix in `O(1)` instead of re-traversing the prefix every time — this is what collapses `O(n²)` down to `O(n)`.

**Core formula to remember:**
```python
mid = i // 2
median = arr[mid]

left_cost  = median * left_cnt  - left_sum
right_cost = right_sum - median * right_cnt

answer[i] = left_cost + right_cost
```

**Don't forget the edge case:** `mid == 0` → no left side exists, guard `prefix[mid - 1]` accordingly.

